"-Health, Safety and Environment (HSE) Gap Analysis and road map/action plan study is monitored and completed;
-The preparation of a national contingency plan is launched;
-TORs to draft HSE legislation, guidelines and standards is finalised and activity is launched; Same for the study to set the Environmental baseline data prioritization and management.
-Consultancy services are procured 1) to conduct cost benefit analysis for the use of gas and low carbon fuels  in the transport sector and in the energy sector (separately); and 2) to conduct a review of legislation and standards;
-Capacity building/awawareness material are produced."

-Health, Safety and Environment (HSE) Gap Analysis consultancy service is finalized, the final consultation workshop is undertaken (100% completed);
-Preparation of NOSCP initiated in August 2015, data collection and meetings with major stakeholders were held in October and November 2015 (30% completed).
-Consultancy services for the preparation of CBAs for the use of natural gas and low carbon fuels in the transport and energy sector initiated: Data collection and analysis as well as meetings with major stakeholders were held (30% completed for both consultancies);
- The ToRs for the procurement of consultancy service to hire a legal expert to assist in the preparation of both CBAs in the transport and energy sector have been posted online. 
-Participated in the International Association for Impact Assessment Conference in April 2015 on the social, economic, and environmental impacts of the oil and gas sector;
-Held continuous meetings with the Norwegian Counterparts under the Oil for Development Program to discuss SODEL outcomes (peer review), areas of collaboration, and to plan for training courses in 2015; Mainly, SODEL participated in the following: 1) Training in Norway with the Norwegian Coastal Administration on Emergency Preparedness and Oil Spill Contingency Planning in October 2015, as part of a Lebanese Delegation, 2) Workshop with the Norwegian Environmental Agency, Department of Oil and Gas in October 2015, to discuss issues related baseline data management, environmental auditing and reporting,  compliance monitoring, EIAs of land based gas processing plants, etc, and 3) Held a meeting with the Norwegian Counterparts to discuss the HSE Gap Analysis Report results and plan the way forward with developing the full HSE Framework. 
-Continuous coordination with the relevant committee in the Ministry of Environment to follow up on SODEL activities, common needs, and future work plans.

-The preparation of a national oil spill contingency plan is monitored and completed. A final consultation workshop will take place;
-preparation of the HSE framework in the Oil  Gas sector in Lebanon is launched;
-Activities to  establish an Environmental Database Structure are maintained;
- Cost benefit analysis studies for the use of gas and low carbon fuels in the energy and transport sectors are completed and policy recommendations are developed; related consultation workshops are conducted;
-The review and update of current legal framework related to the energy and transport sectors in Lebanon is initiated;
-Capacity building and awareness material are produced.

'-The preparation of the HSE framework in the Oil  Gas sector in Lebanon is monitored and completed. Several consultation and validation workshops will take place to develop the framework; 
-Activities to  develop an Environmental Database Structure are established;
- The Cost Benefit Analysis studies for the use of gas in the energy and transport sectors are published.
-The legislative framework study for the transport and energy sectors in Lebanon is completed;
