The Rehabilitation of the Saida Dumpsite Project is 100% completed: 
-The Trash Mountain is gone = all the waste quantities were treated and properly disposed of;   
-The Construction of a sanitary landfill with three cells perfectly isolated with leachate and gas management;    
-The landfill is capped with a geo-membrane liner which is protected by a layer of fine material that is in turn, topped by a layer of artificial grass;    
-A green park of 33,500m2 is constructed with landscape, plantations, irrigation and drainage networks, etc.    
-Awareness campaign in Saida targeted schools’ students, schools’ principals, and local NGOs

